File: A health worker preparing to administer a COVID-19 test. Flickr.com/AIDSVaccine JOHANNESBURG - The number of new COVID-19 infections and deaths continue to decline. The health department said 2,548 new cases were reported on Monday, the lowest in two months. The death toll has increased by 235. WATCH: SA receives first batch of COVID-19 vaccine Most deaths were recorded in the Western Cape, Eastern Cape and Gauteng. The recovery rate has climbed to 89 percent. More than 8.3 million tests have been conducted. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 01 February .
